CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FFour other people were seriously hurt
OL,8,Fin what was Britain's first fatal
OL,9,Fcrash involving multiple trains in
OL,10,Fmore than a quarter of a century.
OL,12,FIt happened near Talerddig in Powys on
OL,13,Fa rural section of the Cambrian line,
OL,14,Fwhich is predominantly single track
OL,15,Fwith loops to allow trains travelling
OL,16,Fin opposite directions to pass each
OL,17,Fother.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FDespite braking, a westbound Transport
OL,8,Ffor Wales (TfW) train failed to stop
OL,9,Fas intended inside a loop and rejoined
OL,10,Fthe single line too soon, crashing
OL,11,Finto an oncoming train run by the same
OL,12,Foperator.
OL,14,FThe RAIB said this happened because
OL,15,Fthe westbound train's wheels were
OL,16,Fsliding, which can be a particular
OL,17,Fissue in autumn when fallen leaves
OL,18,Fmake tracks slippery.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe class 158 trains involved in the
OL,8,Fcrash have two systems ` one automatic
OL,9,Fand one manual ` to dispense sand
OL,10,Fbetween wheels and rails when extra
OL,11,Fgrip is needed.
OL,13,FThe RAIB revealed in an interim report
OL,14,Fin April last year that the westbound
OL,15,Ftrain's automatic system did not work
OL,16,Fin the moments before the crash
OL,17,Fbecause of several failures, including
OL,18,Fblocked hoses, electrical faults and
OL,19,Fincorrectly installed plates measuring
OL,20,Fthe flow rate of sand.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FIn its full report published on
OL,8,FThursday, the RAIB said the driver did
OL,9,Fnot deploy the emergency sanding
OL,10,Fsystem, which is done by pressing a
OL,11,Fyellow plunger in the cab.
OL,13,FThe system discharged sand as expected
OL,14,Fwhen tested after the crash.
OL,16,FInvestigators calculated that the
OL,17,Ftrain would have stopped within the
OL,18,Floop as planned if the manual sander
OL,19,Fwas used when its emergency brake was
OL,20,Factivated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe RAIB said a rule book for TfW
OL,8,Fdrivers states they should deploy the
OL,9,Femergency sander "when a train is
OL,10,Funable to stop in the usual distance"
OL,11,Fand its use may avoid a collision.
OL,13,FBut the driver ` who was not
OL,14,Fidentified in the report ` did not
OL,15,Frecall "any training" on the system
OL,16,Fand had not previously used it,
OL,17,Faccording to the report.
OL,26,@qD@ROUrD@eO]wD@HOUwD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FInvestigators found they were "up to
OL,8,Fdate with their competency
OL,9,Fassessments" at the time of the
OL,10,Faccident.
OL,12,FThe report noted that "they stated
OL,13,Fthat it had not occurred to them to
OL,14,Fuse (the emergency sander) on the
OL,15,Fnight of the accident", which may be
OL,16,Fbecause they initially believed the
OL,17,Ftrain would slow down without further
OL,18,Fintervention.
OL,26,@oD@_OUqD@LO]tD@WOUwD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FAn RAIB survey of other TfW drivers
OL,8,Fafter the accident "revealed a lack of
OL,9,Fclarity" about the circumstances
OL,10,Frequiring the system to be used,
OL,11,Finvestigators said.
OL,13,FThe westbound train travelled
OL,14,Fapproximately 1,080 metres (0.7 miles)
OL,15,Fbeyond its intended stopping position
OL,16,Fbefore the collision.
OL,18,FIt was moving at about 24mph when the
OL,19,Fcrash happened, while the other train
OL,20,Fwas travelling at about 6mph.
OL,26,@pD@TOUqD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FMr Tudor Evans was a passenger on the
OL,8,Fwestbound train.
OL,10,FThree other people on the train `
OL,11,Fincluding the guard ` were seriously
OL,12,Finjured, while at least 18 suffered
OL,13,Fminor injuries.
OL,15,FDamage to the cab of the eastbound
OL,16,Ftrain trapped the driver, who was also
OL,17,Fseriously injured.
OL,19,FThe other five people onboard that
OL,20,Ftrain reported minor injuries.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe report made nine recommendations
OL,8,Faimed about reducing the likelihood
OL,9,Fand mitigating the consequences of a
OL,10,Fsimilar event, including urging TfW to
OL,11,Freview how drivers are trained.
OL,13,FAndrew Hall, the RAIB's chief
OL,14,Finspector of rail accidents, described
OL,15,Fthe Talerddig crash as "a tragedy".
OL,26,@wD@XOUwD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FHe said: "Widely varying levels of
OL,8,Fgrip between steel wheels and steel
OL,9,Frails is an inherent issue for
OL,10,Frailways and a lot of effort goes into
OL,11,Fmanaging this and its possible
OL,12,Fconsequences.
OL,14,F"That can involve the way track and
OL,15,Fthe surrounding area is maintained,
OL,16,Fthe way trains and signalling systems
OL,17,Fare designed, and the way trains are
OL,18,Foperated and maintained.
OL,26,@oD@JOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,F"The Talerddig investigation found
OL,8,Ffactors associated with several of
OL,9,Fthese areas, and related to the way
OL,10,Fdifferent parts of the overall railway
OL,11,Fsystem interacted."
OL,13,FHe added: "I sincerely hope the
OL,14,Flessons of this accident deliver
OL,15,Flasting safety improvements."
OL,17,FTfW and Network Rail said in a joint
OL,18,Fstatement: "Safety remains our highest
OL,19,Fpriority for both our customers and
OL,20,Fcolleagues.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@SO]uD@KOUwD@]O]zD@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,F"Our thoughts continue to be with the
OL,8,Ffamily and loved ones of David Tudor
OL,9,FEvans and those passengers injured in
OL,10,Fthe incident, and we continue to
OL,11,Fsupport our colleagues who were
OL,12,Finjured or affected.
OL,14,F"Network Rail and Transport for Wales
OL,15,Fwelcome the publication of the Rail
OL,16,FAccident Investigation Branch's final
OL,17,Freport into this incident and have co-
OL,18,Foperated fully with the investigation
OL,19,Fthroughout.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781743669
OL,3,CTrain crash could have been avoided if
OL,4,Cdriver had used emergency system `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,F"While incidents of this nature are
OL,8,Fextremely rare on our rail network, we
OL,9,Fremain committed to working together
OL,10,Fas an industry to carefully consider
OL,11,Fthe report's recommendations to help
OL,12,Fprevent a similar incident in the
OL,13,Ffuture."
OL,15,FDave Calfe, general secretary at train
OL,16,Fdrivers' union Aslef, said: "Our
OL,17,Fthoughts are with the family of David
OL,18,FTudor Evans, who tragically lost his
OL,19,Flife that day, and with those who were
OL,20,Finjured, including our member.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@HO]xD@]OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
